SIMPLE: sesqui
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sesqui-
<hw>Ses`qui-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., one half more, one and a
half.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A combining form (also used
adjectively) denoting that <xex>three atoms or equivalents</xex> of the
substance to the name of which it is prefixed are combined with
<xex>two</xex> of some other element or radical; <as>as,
<ex>sesqui</ex>bromide, <ex>sesqui</ex>carbonate,
<ex>sesqui</ex>chloride, <ex>sesqui</ex>oxide</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Sesquidupli-</xex> is sometimes, but rarely, used
in the same manner to denote the proportions of <xex>two and a
half</xex> to <xex>one</xex>, or rather of <xex>five</xex> to
<xex>two</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sesquialter</ent>⟦br⟧
